properties.documentation: Used to specify ranges for qualities that act as <font color="#c93500">Conditions </font>on a Systems' operation.

Describes the <font color="#c93500">Deployment </font>of one or more <font color="#c93500">Systems </font>for a particular purpose. <font color="#c93500">Deployment </font>may be done on a <font color="#c93500">Platform</font>.
A quality of an entity. An aspect of an entity that is intrinsic to and cannot exist without the entity.

An event in the real world that 'triggers' the <font color="#c93500">Sensor</font>. The properties associated to the <font color="#c93500">Stimulus</font> may be different to the eventual observed <font color="#c93500">ObservableProperty</font>. It is the event, not the object, that triggers the <font color="#c93500">Sensor</font>.
Any information that is provided to a <font color="#c93500">Procedure </font>for its use. [MMI OntDev]
Any information that is reported from a <font color="#c93500">Procedure</font>.
System is a unit of abstraction for pieces of infrastructure that implement <font color="#c93500">Procedures</font>. A System may have components, its subsystems, which are other Systems.

The closeness of agreement between the <font color="#c93500">Result </font>of an <font color="#c93500">Observation </font>(resp. the command of an <font color="#c93500">Actuation</font>) and the true value of the observed <font color="#c93500">ObservableProperty </font>(resp. of the acted on <font color="#c93500">ActuatableProperty</font>) under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.

The range of <font color="#c93500">Property </font>values that can be the <font color="#c93500">Result </font>of an <font color="#c93500">Actuation </font>under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.
Total useful life of a <font color="#c93500">System</font>'s battery in the specified <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.
An observed value for which the probability of falsely claiming the absence of a component in a material is beta, given a probability alpha of falsely claiming its presence.

As a <font color="#c93500">Sensor Property</font>: a continuous or incremental change in the reported values of <font color="#c93500">Observations</font> over time for an unchanging <font color="#c93500">Property </font>under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>. As an <font color="#c93500">Actuator Property</font>: a continuous or incremental change in the true value of the acted on <font color="#c93500">ActuatableProperty </font>over time for an unchanging command under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.

The smallest possible time between one <font color="#c93500">Observation</font>, <font color="#c93500">Actuation</font>, or <font color="#c93500">Sampling </font>and the next, under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.

The time between a command for an <font color="#c93500">Observation </font>(resp. <font color="#c93500">Actuation</font>) and the <font color="#c93500">Sensor </font>providing a <font color="#c93500">Result </font>(resp. the <font color="#c93500">Actuator </font>operating the <font color="#c93500">Actuation</font>), under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.
Schedule of maintenance for a <font color="#c93500">System </font>in the specified <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.

The set of values that the <font color="#c93500">Sensor </font>can return as the <font color="#c93500">Result </font>of an <font color="#c93500">Observation </font>under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions </font>with the defined system properties.
Power range in which <font color="#c93500">System </font>is expected to operate in the specified <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.

An identifiable characteristic that represents how the <font color="#c93500">System </font>operates under the specified <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>. May describe power ranges, power sources, standard configurations, attachments and the like.

Describes normal <font color="#c93500">OperatingProperties </font>of a <font color="#c93500">System </font>under some specified <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>. For example, to the power requirement or maintenance schedule of a <font color="#c93500">System </font>under a specified temperature range. In the absence of <font color="#c93500">OperatingProperties</font>, it simply describes the <font color="#c93500">Conditions </font>in which a <font color="#c93500">System </font>is expected to operate. The <font color="#c93500">System </font>continues to operate as defined using <font color="#c93500">SystemCapability</font>. If, however, the <font color="#c93500">OperatingProperty </font>is violated, the System is operating 'out of operating range' and <font color="#c93500">SystemCapability </font>specifications may no longer hold.

The closeness of agreement between replicate <font color="#c93500">Observations </font>on an unchanged or similar quality value: i.e., a measure of a <font color="#c93500">Sensor</font>'s ability to consistently reproduce an <font color="#c93500">Observation</font>, under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.

The closeness of agreement between replicate <font color="#c93500">Actuations </font>for an unchanged or similar command: i.e., a measure of an <font color="#c93500">Actuator</font>'s ability to consistently reproduce an <font color="#c93500">Actuations</font>, under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.

As a <font color="#c93500">Sensor Property</font>: the smallest difference in the value of a <font color="#c93500">ObservableProperty </font>being observed that would result in perceptably different values of <font color="#c93500">Observation Results</font>, under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>. As an <font color="#c93500">Actuator Property</font>: the smallest difference in the value of an <font color="#c93500">Actuation </font>command that would result in a value change of the <font color="#c93500">ActuatableProperty </font>being acted on, under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.

As a <font color="#c93500">Sensor Property</font>: the time between a (step) change in the value of an observed <font color="#c93500">ObservableProperty </font>and a <font color="#c93500">Sensor </font>(possibly with specified error) 'settling' on an observed value, under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>. As an <font color="#c93500">Actuator Property</font>: the time between a (step) change in the command of an <font color="#c93500">Actuator </font>and the 'settling' of the value of the acted on <font color="#c93500">ActuatableProperty</font>, under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.

As a <font color="#c93500">Sensor Property</font>: Selectivity is a <font color="#c93500">Property </font>of a <font color="#c93500">Sensor </font>whereby it provides observed values for one or more <font color="#c93500">ObservableProperties </font>such that the <font color="#c93500">Result </font>for each <font color="#c93500">ObservableProperty </font>are independent of other <font color="#c93500">Properties </font>in the <font color="#c93500">FeatureOfInterest </font>being investigated, under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>. As an <font color="#c93500">Actuator Property</font>: Selectivity is a <font color="#c93500">Property </font>of an <font color="#c93500">Actuator </font>whereby it acts on one or more <font color="#c93500">ActuatableProperties </font>such as the <font color="#c93500">Results </font>for each <font color="#c93500">ActuatableProperty </font>are independent of other <font color="#c93500">Properties </font>in the <font color="#c93500">FeatureOfInterest </font>being acted on, under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.

As a <font color="#c93500">Sensor Property</font>: Sensitivity is the quotient of the change in a <font color="#c93500">Result </font>of <font color="#c93500">Observations </font>and the corresponding change in a value of an <font color="#c93500">ObservableProperty </font>being observed, under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>. As an <font color="#c93500">Actuator Property</font>: Sensitivity is the quotient of the change in a command of <font color="#c93500">Actuation </font>and the corresponding change in a value of an <font color="#c93500">ActuatableProperty </font>being acted on, under the defined <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.

An identifiable characteristic that represents the extent of the <font color="#c93500">System</font>'s useful life under the specified <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>. May describe for example total battery life or number of recharges, or, for <font color="#c93500">Sensors </font>that are used only a fixed number of times, the number of <font color="#c93500">Observations </font>that can be made before the sensing capability is depleted.

Describes <font color="#c93500">SurvivalProperties </font>of a <font color="#c93500">System </font>under some specified <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>. For example, to the lifetime of a System under a specified temperature range. In the absence of <font color="#c93500">SurvivalProperties</font>, simply describes the <font color="#c93500">Conditions </font>a <font color="#c93500">System </font>can be exposed to without damage. For example, the temperature range a System can withstand before being considered damaged. The System continues to operate as defined using <font color="#c93500">SystemCapability</font>. If, however, the SurvivalRange is violated, the <font color="#c93500">System </font>is 'damaged' and <font color="#c93500">SystemCapability </font>specifications may no longer hold.

Describes normal measurement, actuation, sampling properties such as accuracy, range, precision, etc. of a <font color="#c93500">System </font>under some specified <font color="#c93500">Conditions </font>such as a temperature range. The capabilities specified here are those that affect the primary purpose of the <font color="#c93500">System</font>, while those in <font color="#c93500">OperatingRange </font>represent the system's normal operating environment, including <font color="#c93500">Conditions </font>that don't affect the <font color="#c93500">Observations </font>or the <font color="#c93500">Actuations</font>.

Total useful life of a <font color="#c93500">System </font>(expressed as total life since manufacture, time in use, number of operations, etc.) in the specified <font color="#c93500">Conditions</font>.

An identifiable and observable characteristic that represents the <font color="#c93500">System</font>'s ability to operate its primary purpose: a <font color="#c93500">Sensor </font>to make <font color="#c93500">Observations</font>, an <font color="#c93500">Actuator </font>to make <font color="#c93500">Actuations</font>, or a <font color="#c93500">Sampler </font>to make <font color="#c93500">Sampling</font>.
